    "name": "Expositor's Greek Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 26:53",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " gives another reason for not using the sword: if it were God’s will that His Son should be rescued it could be done in a different way. he way suggested is described in military language, the verbs ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "παρακαλεῖν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "παριστάναι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " being both used in classics in connection with military matters, and the word ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "λεγεῶνας",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " suggesting the battalions of the Roman army.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "δώδεκα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", twelve legions, one for each of the twelve disciples.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "πλείω",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", even more than that vast number, Divine resources boundless. The free play of imagination displayed in this conception of a great army of angels evinces the elasticity of Christ’s spirit and His perfect self-possession at a critical moment.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
